    "note": "The submucosa is the toughest layer of the intestine. It can strongly hold sutures, and, therefore, should always be included in an anastomosis. The serosa is the layer whose sutures provide fast healing and, hence, early water-tight anastomosis.",
    "userAnswer": [],
