    "quizId": "sd",
    "category": "Nutrition ",
    "text": "Ten days after right hemicolectomy, a patient develops an external fistula that discharges about I 00ml/day. There is no evidence of sepsis and the patient passes regular daily motions. The suitable method of supplying his nutritional needs is",
